headline.main: HUNGARIAN PACT YUGOSLAV ISSUE; Accord, Urged by Germany, Is Opposed in Belgrade as Curb on Free Action AIMS BAFFLE OBSERVERS Csaky Expected for Parley-- Secret Talk With Hitler Reported and Denied

lead_paragraph: BELGRADE, Yugoslavia, Dec. 2 --Count Stephen Csaky, the Hungarian Foreign Minister, is expected to arrive in Belgrade some time this week. His trip is connected with the forthcoming conclusion of a Hungarian-Yugoslav pact of friendship, similar to that existing between this country and Bulgaria.
